dcterms:description: A dataset of handwritten digits, commonly used for training various image processing systems. It consists of 60,000 training images and 10,000 testing images of 28x28 grayscale images of digits from 0 to 9.
dcterms:title: MNIST

dcterms:description: A synthetic dataset consisting of randomly generated 2D points, used for testing and analyzing the behavior of neural networks in memorization tasks.
dcterms:title: Random 2D points
